    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but isn't the \"dynamic framework\" thing just a way to say the law doesn't actually exist? if we can't rely on the text itself, then the law is just whatever the judges feel like doing that day. isn't it more intellectually honest to say that originalism is the only way to prevent the court from becoming a political body?",
